sentences: Loren Nerell (born November 30, 1960) is an American composer and performer of ambient American music and Balinese gamelan.

He spent several months in Java and Bali studying native styles of gamelan music, some of which he has performed in the greater Los Angeles area with other gamelan enthusiasts.
With it, he crossed over into a world of music that previously did not exist for him.
Loren currently works in UCLA's Herb Alpert School of Music as a recording technician.
